'''Carrot and stick''' is a term used to refer to the act of simultaneously rewarding good behaviour while punishing bad behaviour.

{{Vocab-stub}}
[[de:Zuckerbrot und Peitsche]]
[[eo:Flato kaj bato]]
[[vi:Cây gậy và củ cà rốt]]
This definition seems to have changed considerably over the years.  In my youth, "carrot and stick" referred to the idea of dangling a carrot from a stick with a piece of string, then sitting on a stubborn burro's back and holding the carrot in front of the burro in order to get him to move.  The burro would walk forward thinking he was going to reach the carrot.

The meaning of course was that you can get someone to do what you want by holding something valuable in front of him, not using the stick to hit him.